# 👥 Customer Segmentation using K-Means Clustering

## 📌 Objective
The objective of this project is to segment customers into different groups based on their purchasing behavior using the K-Means Clustering algorithm.

---

## 📂 Dataset
- Mall Customers Dataset
- Source: Kaggle

---

## 🛠️ What I Did

### 1. Data Loading
- Loaded the dataset.
- Explored dataset structure.

### 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Checked missing values.
- Removed unnecessary columns.
- Analyzed customer information.

### 3. Data Preprocessing
- Encoded categorical features.
- Standardized numerical data using StandardScaler.

### 4. Dimensionality Reduction
- Applied Principal Component Analysis (PCA) for visualization.

### 5. Finding Optimal Clusters
- Used the Elbow Method.
- Evaluated clusters using Silhouette Score.

### 6. K-Means Clustering
- Built the K-Means model.
- Assigned customers to different clusters.

### 7. Cluster Analysis
- Calculated average values for each cluster.
- Interpreted customer characteristics.
- Created customer personas.

### 8. Data Visualization
- Scatter Plot
- Cluster Visualization
- PCA Visualization
- Elbow Curve

---

